Real-World Example

A sales manager reviews the pipeline every Friday.

Everything appears healthy.

Three days later, a major opportunity is marked as Closed Lost.

Looking back, the warning signs were already there:

No customer activity for 18 days.
Close date changed four times.
No next meeting scheduled.
No executive engagement.

The information existed.

No one saw it soon enough.

That's visibility leakage.

Revenue Systems Insight

Revenue leaders don't need more dashboards.

